This paper is about personalized dialogue learning, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper proposes a meta-learning approach, which is a type of machine learning algorithm, so cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a likely sub-category. The paper also involves training a model to adapt quickly to new personas, which requires a certain level of generalization, making cs.LG (Learning) another possible sub-category. The paper also involves training a model on a small amount of data, which is a common challenge in NLP, making cs.SD (Sound) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves training a model to improve dialogue consistency, which is a common goal in reinforcement learning, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another possible sub-category.
